    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="146"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2222/14008</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">17 October, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I know you will be pleased to
                    read the enclosed. I suggest that you make immediate arrangements with the War
                    Department for the action suggested.</p>
                <p>Cordially and sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Enclosure]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="from">
                            <hi rend="italic">Crowell</hi>
                        </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                                >Wilson</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-10">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 10, 1918.</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: In reply to your letter of
                        October 7th<note n="25" xml:id="d146fn1">Not printed.</note> inclosing a
                        letter from the Secretary of State of October 5th, in which it is proposed
                        that the subjects of Turkey, for the purposes of the administration of the
                        Draft Act, be treated as though they were alien enemies, I have the honor to
                        inform you that I agree fully with the Secretary of State as to the
                        advisability of taking the action he proposes.</p>
                    <p>Cordially yours,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Benedict Crowell</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
